# 🐧 Linux Commands Practice & System Exploration

This repository documents hands-on practice with essential Linux commands, covering system navigation, file management, user management, process monitoring, and log analysis.

---

## 📌 Objective

To gain practical experience with:

* Linux file system navigation
* System monitoring commands
* User and permission management
* Log analysis
* Archive handling

---

## 🖥️ Environment Details

* OS: Linux (Ubuntu-based)
* User: `root`
* Working Directory: `/var/log`

---

## 📂 1. File System Navigation

```bash
ls
pwd
cd /
cd ~
cd /var
cd /var/log
cd ..
```

✔ Learned:

* Moving across directories
* Understanding root (`/`) and home (`~`)
* Navigating system folders like `/etc`, `/var/log`

---

## 📄 2. File Viewing & Reading

```bash
cat /etc/os-release
cat /etc/passwd
less
more
head -n 5 abc
```

✔ Learned:

* Viewing file contents
* Difference between `cat`, `less`, `more`
* Reading system configuration files

---

## 👤 3. User & System Info Commands

```bash
who
whoami
id
hostname
hostname -i
uname
uname -a
uptime
```

✔ Learned:

* Current user and system identity
* Kernel and OS details
* System uptime

---

## 🌐 4. Network Commands

```bash
curl ifconfig.me
ping
netstat
```

✔ Learned:

* Fetch public IP
* Check connectivity
* Inspect network status

---

## ⚙️ 5. Process & Resource Monitoring

```bash
top
ps
ps -ef
free
free -h
df
df -h
du
```

✔ Learned:

* Monitor CPU & memory usage
* View running processes
* Disk usage analysis

---

## 📦 6. File & Directory Management

```bash
mkdir myfiles
rm myfiles
rmdir myfiles
ls -l
chmod 755 allfiles.tar
```

✔ Learned:

* Create and remove directories
* Understand file permissions
* Use `chmod`

---

## 📁 7. Archive Handling

```bash
tar -cvf allfiles.tar myfiles
tar -xvf allfiles.tar
```

✔ Learned:

* Create tar archives
* Extract files

---

## 🔐 8. User & Password Management

```bash
passwd
cat /etc/shadow
```

✔ Learned:

* Change passwords
* Understand secure password storage

⚠️ Note: `/etc/shadow` requires root access.

---

## 📜 9. Log Monitoring (Important for DevOps)

```bash
cd /var/log
ls
cat auth.log
cat auth.log | grep error
tail auth.log
tail -n 50 auth.log
tail -f auth.log
```

✔ Learned:

* Monitor authentication logs
* Filter logs using `grep`
* Real-time log tracking with `tail -f`

---

## 🔎 10. Search & Utility Commands

```bash
locate
history
clear
```

✔ Learned:

* Search files quickly
* Track command history
* Clean terminal

---

## ⚠️ Common Mistakes Observed

```bash
del myfiles          # ❌ Not valid in Linux
rmdir my files       # ❌ Space issue
cat etc/password     # ❌ Wrong path
cd /etc/shadow       # ❌ It's a file, not directory
```

✔ Fix:

* Use correct Linux syntax
* Always verify file paths

